1. This is a readme file for the developer.

2. Install
checkout this directory in your desired location and update your $PATH to /release/bin directory so you can test.

3. Work on java code
Open eclipse with the spoofax plug-in installed and set your workspace to /java.
You can run the K3Java project to test the main functionalities directly from eclipse, or you can build the .jar binaries by calling ant on /java/K3Java/buld.xml

4. Work on maude code
Build the .jar binaries by calling ant on /java/K3Java/buld.xml.
Modify the maude files found in /release/maude

5. Build the final release zip
Call ant on /buildrelease.xml